	<!-- properties -->
	<element name="Ammunition" type="Weapon Property" source="Internal" id="ID_WOTC_DMG_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_AMMUNITION">
		<description>
			<p>The ammunition of a firearm is destroyed upon use. Renaissance and modern firearms use bullets. Futuristic firearms are powered by a special type of ammunition called energy cells. An energy cell contains enough power for all the shots its firearm can make.</p>
		</description>
	</element>
	<element name="Burst Fire" type="Weapon Property" source="Internal" id="ID_WOTC_DMG_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_BURST_FIRE">
		<description>
			<p>A weapon that has the burst fire property can make a normal single-target attack, or it can spray a 10-foot-cube area within normal range with shots. Each creature in the area must succeed on a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw or take the weapon's normal damage. This action uses ten pieces of ammunition.</p>
		</description>
	</element>
	<element name="Reload" type="Weapon Property" source="Internal" id="ID_WOTC_DMG_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FIREARM_RELOAD">
		<description>
			<p>A limited number of shots can be made with a weapon that has the reload property. A character must then reload it using an action or a bonus action (the character's choice).</p>
		</description>
	</element>

